@startuml
title Chat Completions Request (End-to-End)

skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam participantPadding 15
skinparam BoxPadding 10
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

participant "LLM Gateway" as Gateway

box "Stargate Pod" #f0f7e8
  participant "HTTP Proxy\n:8000" as Proxy
  participant "Load Balancer\nRouter" as LB
  participant "QUIC Tunnel\nClient" as QuicProxy
end box

box "pylon" #e8f4fd
  participant "QUIC Tunnel\nServer" as TunnelSvr
end box

participant "Inference Server\n/v1/chat/completions" as Upstream

== Request ==
Gateway -> Proxy: POST /v1/chat/completions\nx-routing-key: my-rk\nx-model: my-model\nx-request-id: req-42\nx-input-tokens: 128\nContent-Type: application/json\n\n{"messages":[...],"stream":true}

note over Proxy
  Extracts x-model (required) and
  x-routing-key (optional) to build
  RoutingTargetKey. x-input-tokens
  is required. Body is opaque -- never parsed.
end note

Proxy -> LB: cluster_candidates_for_target(\n  RoutingTargetKey{my-rk, my-model})
LB --> Proxy: [cluster-A (rtt=5ms), cluster-B (rtt=12ms)]

note over LB
  Default: power-of-two
  (sample 2, pick lower prompt-work time).
  Only clusters with a backend that has an open QUIC
  connection and a healthy RTT
  sample are candidates.
end note

Proxy -> LB: choose(LoadBalancerRequest, candidates)
LB --> Proxy: cluster-A
Proxy -> Proxy: select concrete backend\nserver-A in cluster-A

== QUIC Tunnel ==
Proxy -> QuicProxy: proxy_request_streaming(\n  "server-A",\n  POST, "/v1/chat/completions",\n  forwarded headers, body)

QuicProxy -> QuicProxy: look up pooled QUIC\nconnection for server-A

QuicProxy -> TunnelSvr: open_bi() on existing\nQUIC connection

note over QuicProxy,TunnelSvr
  Raw QUIC path shown below: Cap'n Proto
  tunnel frames carry headers and body.
  HTTP/3 uses an H3 request stream.
  WebTransport uses its HTTP proxy head
  blocks plus raw body bytes, not Raw QUIC frames.
end note

QuicProxy -> TunnelSvr: send_header(\n  x-method: POST,\n  x-path: /v1/chat/completions,\n  x-model, x-request-id, ...)
QuicProxy -> TunnelSvr: send_body(request body chunks)
QuicProxy -> TunnelSvr: finish (half-close)

== Upstream ==
TunnelSvr -> Upstream: POST /v1/chat/completions\n(reconstructed HTTP request)
Upstream --> TunnelSvr: HTTP 200\nContent-Type: text/event-stream\n\ndata: {"choices":[...]}\ndata: {"choices":[...]}\ndata: [DONE]

== Response ==
TunnelSvr -> QuicProxy: send_header(x-status: 200,\n  content-type, ...)
TunnelSvr -> QuicProxy: send_body(SSE chunks)

QuicProxy --> Proxy: StreamingResponse {\n  status: 200,\n  headers,\n  body_stream }

note over Proxy
  Adds response headers:
  x-inference-server-id: server-A
  x-stargate-cluster-id: cluster-A
  Copies forwardable upstream headers.
  Records TTFB and metrics.
end note

Proxy --> Gateway: HTTP 200\nx-inference-server-id: server-A\nx-stargate-cluster-id: cluster-A\nContent-Type: text/event-stream\n\ndata: {"choices":[...]}\ndata: {"choices":[...]}\ndata: [DONE]

@enduml
